---
import { SITE } from '../consts';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title={SITE.title} description={SITE.description} activePath="/" wide>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="surface">
      <p class="eyebrow">Personal Website</p>
      <h1 class="page-title">Duo Sun</h1>
      <p class="page-lead">
        Economics student in the UK with a growing body of work around finance,
        technology, research, and careful long-form thinking.
      </p>

      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button" href="/cv">View CV</a>
        <a class="button button--secondary" href="/posts">Read Posts</a>
        <a class="button button--secondary" href="/contact">Get in Touch</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="surface surface--accent">
      <p class="eyebrow">Current Focus</p>
      <h2 class="card-title">Building a solid public profile</h2>
      <p>
        This site is the central place for my background, writing, and contact
        details. The goal is clarity: one clean home for who I am, what I work
        on, and where to reach me.
      </p>

      <ul class="stat-list">
        <li class="stat">
          <strong>Base</strong>
          UK
        </li>
        <li class="stat">
          <strong>Focus</strong>
          Finance and research
        </li>
        <li class="stat">
          <strong>Format</strong>
          Static Astro site
        </li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Overview</p>
        <h2 class="card-title">What this website is for</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        A stable personal website should introduce your work quickly, point
        people to the right page, and feel credible without becoming complex.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid--3">
      <article class="surface">
        <p class="eyebrow">Background</p>
        <h3 class="card-title">About</h3>
        <p>
          Learn about my academic path, interests, and the themes that shape my
          work.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="surface">
        <p class="eyebrow">Profile</p>
        <h3 class="card-title">CV</h3>
        <p>
          A structured summary of education, experience, practical skills, and
          professional direction.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="surface">
        <p class="eyebrow">Writing</p>
        <h3 class="card-title">Posts</h3>
        <p>
          Notes, essays, and short pieces that document what I am learning and
          thinking about.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Explore</p>
        <h2 class="card-title">Start here</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        Each page has a distinct purpose, but they now share one visual system
        and one clear navigation structure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid--2">
      <a class="surface link-card" href="/about">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h3 class="card-title">Personal background and interests</h3>
        <p>
          A more complete introduction to who I am, how I work, and what I care
          about.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a class="surface link-card" href="/cv">
        <p class="eyebrow">CV</p>
        <h3 class="card-title">Formal experience and education</h3>
        <p>
          The concise professional view for collaborators, recruiters, and
          academic contacts.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a class="surface link-card" href="/posts">
        <p class="eyebrow">Posts</p>
        <h3 class="card-title">Writing and public notes</h3>
        <p>
          Short static posts published from local Markdown files and built into
          the site.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a class="surface link-card" href="/contact">
        <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
        <h3 class="card-title">Email and online presence</h3>
        <p>
          The fastest ways to reach me for opportunities, conversations, or
          project-related questions.
        </p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
